# Brand Architecture

## The two-brand system

**The House We Built (THWB)** and **Trellis** are two brands
owned by one company. Each does a different job. Each has its
own home. Together they form a content-plus-product system.

## What each brand is

### The House We Built

**What it is:** The media and content brand. The story. The
philosophy.

**What it includes:**
- The podcast (The House We Built, weekly/bi-weekly)
- Essays and long-form writing by Remi and Kendra
- The framework — the 11 pillars in rich philosophical form
- The Sunday letter (newsletter)
- The family's story
- Future: courses, books, speaking, possibly a conference

**Who runs it:** Kendra (primary). Remi contributes essays when
relevant. She holds editorial direction, voice, content cadence.

**Domain:** thehousewebuilt.family

**Purpose in the funnel:** Top. Trust-building. Audience
development. Discovery. Warm readers who may eventually convert
to Trellis subscribers.

**Revenue:** None directly in year one. Potential future streams
include paid newsletter tier, courses, speaking, books.

**Aesthetic:** Cream dominant. Forest accents. Magazine/editorial.
Kinfolk meets Every.to. Slow internet.

### Trellis

**What it is:** The software product. The app. The operating
system.

**What it includes:**
- The authenticated app at trellis.family/app
- The marketing site at trellis.family
- 11 pillars of household leadership
- Cy (AI family steward)
- Family Meeting
- Kid view
- Task system
- Content library (essays and frameworks served inside pillars,
  sourced from THWB writing)

**Who runs it:** Remi (primary). Product, engineering, customer
experience, growth.

**Domain:** trellis.family (and trellisfamily.com for typo
protection)

**Purpose in the funnel:** Bottom. Conversion. Revenue.

**Revenue:** Direct. $29/mo per family or $290/year. This is the
monetization engine.

**Aesthetic:** Forest dark dominant. Gold accent. Cream text.
Oura meets Notion. Warm but capable. Tech-respectable but not
techy.

## How they relate

**THWB content FEEDS Trellis pillars.**

Every essay Kendra writes about partnership communication can
live inside Pillar 02 (The Partnership) in the Trellis app.
Every podcast episode about rhythm can live inside Pillar 04
(Time and Rhythms). Every framework piece about money can live
inside Pillar 05 (Money and Stewardship).

The THWB content library becomes Trellis subscription value.
Paying families get access to everything.

Non-paying visitors to thehousewebuilt.family can read most
content free. This is intentional. Generosity drives trust.
Trellis monetizes the depth and the tool, not the writing.

